This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a supervised learning method based on deep distributed random samplings. It also mentions the similarity and differences with random forests, which is a popular machine learning algorithm. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields often use machine learning techniques. The use of nearest neighbor optimization in the proposed method may also suggest a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on coding and dimensionality reduction may also place it in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
